                    DHSP    Mail Code  726    Office Hours  By appointment    Related Sites  Assistive Technology Unit     About  Mr. Hedman has been a clinical rehabilitation engineer in the Chicago area since 1983. He served as director of rehabilitation engineering at the Rehabilitation Institute of Chicago from 1984 to 1989, and has served as director of the UIC Assistive Technology Unit since 1989.     Education  MS in Civil Engineering, University of Illinois at Chicago MEng in Mechanical Engineering, University of Virginia BS in Bioengineering, University of Illinois at Chicago  Certifications: Licensed Professional Engineer (PE) Certified Professional Ergonomist (CPE) RESNA Assistive Technology Professional (ATP)           Disability and Human Development    Back to main content           Admissions and Programs    Expand Admissions and Programs menu          Minor in Disability and Human Development    BS in Disability and Human Development    Expand BS in Disability and Human Development menu          What to Expect    Before You Apply    Applying    Expand Applying menu          Transferring from another UIC program      After You Apply      MS in Disability and Human Development    PhD in Disability Studies    Expand PhD in Disability Studies menu          What to Expect    Before You Apply    Applying    After You Apply    Faculty    Meet Our Students      Assistive Technology Certificate    Expand Assistive Technology Certificate menu          What to Expect    Applying    Faculty    Assistive Technology Certificate FAQ      Disability Ethics Certificate    Expand Disability Ethics Certificate menu          What to Expect    Applying        Institute on Disability and Human Development    Community Partners    Expand Community Partners menu          Bodies of Work      Research Centers, Clinics and Community Programs    Continuing Education and Community Training    News    Calendar    Directory    Contact              Follow Disability and Human Devel